        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This collection consists chiefly of 600 letters and written to and from George Watt during World War II. There is also a page proof of Watt's book   (1990). First donation: seven handwritten World War II era letters. Five are from George Watt, then in the US Army; three of these are to Milt Wolff. Two letters are about George Watt. Also included is a page proof of Watt's book   (1990). Second donation (Dec. 2004): c. 300 letters written by George Watt during World War II to his wife, Margaret Watt. Third donation: (Dec. 2005): c. 300 World War II letters to and from George Watt (some from his wife, Margaret Watt, and some from Milt Wolff) and miscellaneous documents.</p>
